def custom_sort_list_mixed_types(my_list: List[Union[int, float, str]]) -> Tuple[List[Union[int, float]], List[str]]:
    num_list = [i for i in my_list if isinstance(i, (int, float))]
    str_list = [i for i in my_list if isinstance(i, str)]

    # Sorting num_list
    for i in range(len(num_list)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(num_list)):
            if num_list[i]>num_list[j]:
                num_list[i], num_list[j] = num_list[j], num_list[i]

    # Sorting str_list
    for i in range(len(str_list)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(str_list)):
            if str_list[i]>str_list[j]:
                str_list[i], str_list[j] = str_list[j], str_list[i]

    return num_list, str_list
```
This function first separates the input list into two lists. Then, it sorts each list using a simple comparison-based approach. The time complexity of this function is O(n^2), where n is the length of the input list. It would be more efficient to use a more advanced sorting algorithm, but this approach is simple and easy to understand.

